Personal Life

Michael C Hall has been married twice: first to Amy Spangler, and then later to Dexter co-star Jennifer Carpenter. Both marriages ended in divorce. In 2010, Hall revealed that he was undergoing treatment for Hodgkin's lymphoma, and attended that year's Golden Globe awards wearing a knitted cap to cover his chemotherapy related hair loss. However, later that year he announced that he was fully recovered.

description: Gregbo Watson is a comic artist and illustrator with a twisted imagination and dark sense of humor. Both of which are mirrored in his art and illustration style. His work is heavily influenced by the many ghostly legends and southern folktales he was raised on during his childhood. Spooky stories filled with offbeat characters, wicked witches, ghosts and goblins fascinated his imagination.
name: Gregbo Watson

description:
John Gomes is an illustrator and comic artist based in the San Francisco Bay Area, who has his BFA in Illustration from the Academy of Art University in San Francisco. He has been drawing for as long as he can remember and grew up obsessively recreating his favorite comic characters (mainly X-men) and cartoons (Dino-Riders and Johnny Quest). His work has been published in comics and mobile gaming and has been featured in the Academy of Art’s juried Spring Show of 2012, 2013, and 2014.

When not working on projects John enjoys catching up on his favorite soccer teams, attempting to learn bass, and reading up on the latest comic story lines.
name: John Gomes

deck: An American actress known for playing Gamora and Nyota Uhura.
description:
Biography

Born in New Jersey, Zoe moved with her family to the Dominican Republic and studied dance there before moving back at age 17. Her dancing, coupled with stage acting, helped land her first role, 2000's "Center Stage."

Comic Book Movie Roles

Zoe landed the role of Uhura in J.J. Abrams' 2009 "Star Trek," which she reprised in 2013's sequel "Star Trek: Into Darkness." She also played Aisha in the 2010 movie "The Losers". She played Gamora in the 2014 movie "Guardians of the Galaxy," and is expected to reprise her role in the 2017 sequel.
name: Zoe Saldana
